result.execSummary:
Tevin T. Wellington was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Tevin T. Wellington was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 9:46 AM case called. Prosecuting Attorney Loralee Clark in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Tevin T. Wellington in court in custody without counsel. State indicates Florida has mailed Governor's warrant. State requests new date to wait for receipt of warrant. Court extends time limit for good cause. Defendant indicates he would like to waive extradition. Court reschedules at 11:00 on 7/20/2022.

(11:02 AM case called.) Prosecuting attorney Loralee Clark in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Tevin T. Wellington in court, in custody without counsel.
State notes has received a signed Governor's Warrant on the defendant.
Defendant advises is not contesting his identity and does not wish to further fight extradition.
Defendant requests to post bond if able to raise the money and Court informs the defendant he will be held until the Governor's warrant is satisfied and he is transported.
Defendant advises is not contesting or challenging the Governor's Warrant or extradition.
Defendant held until transport is arranged and completed.

Florida has not filed a Governor's Warrant yet. State is working with Miami Dade County. State requests more time for paperwork to be completed. There is a cash bond in place.

(11:09 AM case called.) Prosecuting attorney Afton Brianna Lewis in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Tevin T. Wellington appeared by video, in custody in the Eau Claire County Jail. Attorney Sonia L Anderson appeared by video for Tevin T. Wellington.
Defendant acknowledges receipt of the complaint.
State requests high cash bond or no bond at all. Attorney Anderson requests signature bond or low cash bond.
